# INCREMENT 11a — Synastry Page Implementation Plan

> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.

**Goal:** Implement the Synastry comparison page (`/synastry`) that loads two separate profiles, computes Wu-Xing compatibility, BaZi Day Master resonance, and western cross-chart aspects — all client-side from existing profile data. Second person is always optional.

**Architecture:** Export `createSynastryProjection(profileA, profileB)` from `projections.js` (returns a purpose-built shape, not the DomainProjection type used by single-profile pages). `SynastryPage.js` owns its own two-person input flow: two mini-forms side by side, "Beide berechnen" button, then three sections. Route `/synastry` wired in `app.js`. Second input optional — Section 4 (Extension G placeholder) renders a "coming soon" card.

**Tech Stack:** Vanilla ES modules, `node:test`, `node:assert/strict`. No new dependencies.

---

## Context you need

**`public/src/domain/projections.js`** exports four projection functions, each returning `DomainProjection = { primaryFactors, supportingFactors, missingFactors, sourceTrace, confidence }`. This plan adds a fifth export `createSynastryProjection` with a different return shape suited for cross-profile comparison.

**ViewModel body longitudes** — `normalizeAzodiacResult` in `server.js` (line ~254) writes `longitude: Number(body.longitude ?? body.lon ?? body.degree ?? 0)` for each body in `western.bodies`. Longitudes are always present in the ViewModel but may be 0 when upstream omits them.

**Test pattern** — `test/projections.test.js` imports named exports from `public/src/domain/projections.js` directly (no DOM, no server). Add new tests to the same file.

**Existing pages** follow pattern: `export function XxxPage(app, { profile, onNavigate })`, set `app.innerHTML`, then imperatively wire DOM. For Synastry the signature is `export function SynastryPage(app, { onNavigate })` — no pre-loaded profile, page manages its own two-person fetch.

**GeoInput** — `GeoInput({ onSelect })` returns a DOM node; `onSelect` receives `{ display, lat, lon, tz }` or `null` when selection is cleared.

**`calculateProfile`** — imported from `../api/client.js`; takes `{ date, time, lat, lon, tz }`, returns `{ ok, data, status, error }`.

**Route registration** — in `public/src/app.js`, no profile guard needed for Synastry (it fetches its own data).

**Run a single test file:**
```bash
node --test test/projections.test.js
```

**Run full suite:**
```bash
node --test test/*.test.js
```

Expected total when all pass: `# fail 0`.

