### Task 8: I4 — TransitCalendarPage: CSS classes instead of inline API-derived style

**Files:**
- Modify: `public/src/pages/TransitCalendarPage.js:103-106`
- Modify: `public/src/styles/main.css` (append intensity bar styles)

**Context:** `renderTimeline` writes `style="height:${Math.round(v * 100)}%;opacity:${Math.max(0.3, v)}"` where `v` is an API value. This puts API-derived content into an HTML attribute without escaping. Fix: bucket `v` into 3 CSS classes (`tdi-bar--low`, `tdi-bar--mid`, `tdi-bar--high`) and define the heights/opacities in CSS. No API data touches the DOM attribute string.

**Step 1: Update renderTimeline in TransitCalendarPage.js**

In `public/src/pages/TransitCalendarPage.js`, replace lines 102-107:

```javascript
// BEFORE:
      <div class="transit-day-intensity">
        ${(day.sector_intensity || []).map((v, i) =>
          v > 0.15
            ? `<span class="tdi-bar" title="${i + 1}. Haus" style="height:${Math.round(v * 100)}%;opacity:${Math.max(0.3, v)}"></span>`
            : '<span class="tdi-bar tdi-bar--empty"></span>'
        ).join('')}
      </div>
```

Replace with:
```javascript
      <div class="transit-day-intensity">
        ${(day.sector_intensity || []).map((v, i) => {
          const level = typeof v === 'number' && Number.isFinite(v)
            ? v > 0.6 ? 'high' : v > 0.3 ? 'mid' : v > 0.15 ? 'low' : 'empty'
            : 'empty';
          return level === 'empty'
            ? `<span class="tdi-bar tdi-bar--empty" title="${i + 1}. Haus"></span>`
            : `<span class="tdi-bar tdi-bar--${level}" title="${i + 1}. Haus"></span>`;
        }).join('')}
      </div>
```

